%20not%20only%20undermining%20the%20two%20ministries%20he%20is%20in%20charge%20of%20but%20also%20fueling%20sentiments%20dangerous%20to%20the%20institutions%20that%20have%20been%20laboriously%20built.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPresumption%20of%20guilt%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20minister%E2%80%99s%20comment%20essentially%20tells%20the%20young%20law%20students%20to%20assume%20an%20accused%20as%20guilty%20and%20pass%20a%20moral%20judgment%20on%20an%20accused%20based%20on%20what%20he%20has%20been%20charged%20with%20by%20an%20investigating%20agency.%20Adjudicating%20somebody%20as%20guilty%20simply%20based%20on%20information%20collected%20by%20the%20investigating%20agency%20is%20in%20itself%20problematic.%20The%20assumption%20of%20guilt%20is%20also%20fundamentally%20at%20odds%20with%20India%E2%80%99s%20criminal%20and%20constitutional%20law%2C%20which%20presumes%20innocence%20before%20convicting%20an%20individual.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20statement%20also%20severely%20undermines%20the%20purpose%20of%20establishing%20the%20prominent%20National%20Law%20Universities%20in%20India%2C%20which%20were%20established%20in%20the%201980s%20to%20create%20specialised%20schools%20dealing%20with%20and%20engaging%20with%20the%20law%20and%20to%20create%20an%20excellent%20stream%20of%20lawyers%20who%20would%20serve%20the%20cause%20of%20justice%20and%20contribute%20to%20making%20the%20law%20accessible%20to%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F15124522%2Fpexels-sora-shimazaki-5668473.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F15124522%2Fpexels-sora-shimazaki-5668473.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F15124522%2Fpexels-sora-shimazaki-5668473-300x150.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F15124522%2Fpexels-sora-shimazaki-5668473-1024x512.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F15124522%2Fpexels-sora-shimazaki-5668473-800x400.jpg%20800w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-689285%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERepresentative%20image.%20Photo%3A%20Sora%20Shimazaki%2FPexels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20minister%20appears%20to%20seek%20to%20reverse%20that%20by%20training%20a%20new%20generation%20of%20young%20lawyers%20in%20India%20to%20believe%20everything%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20investigative%20agencies%20say.%20What%20is%20problematic%20is%20the%20argument%20that%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20terrorism%2C%20we%20should%20all%20agree%20to%20disregard%20the%20guarantees%20of%20the%20constitution%20that%20entitle%20every%20accused%20to%20legal%20representation%20and%20a%20fair%20trial.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20claiming%20that%20it%20is%20%E2%80%98ethical%E2%80%99%20not%20to%20take%20on%20such%20cases%20because%20it%20%E2%80%98damages%E2%80%99%20the%20country%2C%20young%20lawyers%20are%20being%20asked%20to%20forsake%20their%20legal%20and%20constitutional%20duty%20to%20defend%20the%20accused.%20The%20statement%20of%20the%20minister%20essentially%20shows%20the%20impatience%20with%20due%20process%20of%20law%20and%20the%20increasing%20impunity%20afforded%20to%20those%20who%20claim%20themselves%20to%20be%20the%20custodians%20of%20national%20security.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIncrease%20in%20the%20use%20of%20anti-terror%20laws%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20is%20fundamentally%20incorrect%20here%20is%20the%20idea%20that%20all%20people%20charged%20with%20terrorism%20are%20%E2%80%98terrorists%E2%80%99.%20The%20desire%20to%20push%20this%20story%20stems%20from%20the%20current%20government%E2%80%99s%20desperation%2C%20as%20there%20has%20been%20a%20surge%20in%20terrorism%20cases%20brought%20against%20students%2C%20activists%2C%20and%20journalists%2C%20among%20others.%20One%20merely%20needs%20to%20look%20at%20the%20rise%20in%20anti-terror%20laws%20and%20Unlawful%20Activities%20(Prevention)%20Act%20(UAPA)%20cases%20in%20recent%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20NCRB%E2%80%99s%202022%20crime%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheprint.in%2Findia%2Fncrb-data-shows-uapa-cases-increased-by-23-in-2022-while-those-under-sedition-down-by-nearly-75%2F1871719%2F%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20there%20has%20been%20a%2017.9%25%20increase%20in%20UAPA%2C%20with%20a%20total%20of%201%2C005%20cases%20documented%20across%20the%20country%20in%202022.%20This%20represents%20a%20significant%20increase%20from%202021%2C%20when%20814%20instances%20were%20reported%2C%20to%20796%20cases%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurthermore%2C%20the%20very%20low%20number%20of%20convictions%20in%20these%20cases%20shows%20how%20unfairly%20and%20viciously%20people%20are%20punished%20in%20these%20cases%2C%20forcing%20them%20to%20spend%20years%20in%20prison%20because%20bail%20is%20impossible%20to%20obtain.%20In%20most%20cases%2C%20the%20botched-up%20investigation%20damages%20the%20crucial%20years%20of%20persons%20accused%20under%20these%20severe%20laws.%20According%20to%20data%20released%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thequint.com%2Fnews%2Fpolitics%2Fmonsoon-session-parliament-4690-people-arrested-under-uapa-from-2018-2020-only-149-convicted-government%23read-more%5C%22%3EMinistry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20of%204%2C690%20people%20arrested%20between%202018%20and%202020%2C%20only%203%25%20were%20convicted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20liberty%20of%20a%20citizen%20is%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20a%20constitutional%20democracy%2C%20and%20we%20need%20both%20a%20watchful%20judiciary%20providing%20a%20check%20and%20balance%20on%20the%20unrestricted%20powers%20of%20investigating%20a