l%20in%20Colorado%20in%202011%20(right).%20%3Cp%3EDateability%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EJacqueline%20Child%2C%2029%2C%20had%20bad%20experiences%20on%20dating%20apps%20for%20years%20because%20of%20her%20disabilities.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIn%202021%2C%20she%20and%20her%20sister%20Alexa%2C%2033%2C%20co-founded%20a%20dating%20app%20for%20people%20with%20disabilities.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20says%20the%20app%20has%20given%20her%20purpose%20and%20helped%20her%20feel%20more%20confident%20in%20herself.%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20is%20an%20as-told-to%20essay%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Jacqueline%20Child%2C%20co-founder%20of%20Dateability%2C%20a%20dating%20app%20for%20disabled%20people.%20The%20essay%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20disabled%20since%20I%20was%2014%20when%20I%20developed%20a%20chronic%20illness.%20At%2029%2C%20I've%20had%20over%2040%20surgeries%20to%20treat%20more%20than%20six%20medical%20conditions%20that%20affect%20every%20part%20of%20my%20body%2C%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Flupus-signs-symptoms-2018-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elupus%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20dysautonomia.%20I%20live%20with%20severe%20chronic%20pain%20and%20eat%20through%20a%20feeding%20tube%2C%20but%20my%20disability%20is%20largely%20invisible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20big%20adjustment%20going%20from%20being%20healthy%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspoon-theory-spoonie-community-chronic-illness-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echronically%20ill%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ebut%20over%20time%2C%20as%20I%20learned%20to%20focus%20on%20the%20other%20things%20in%20my%20life%20and%20manage%20my%20symptoms%20very%20well%2C%20it%20got%20easier.%20One%20thing%20that%20remained%20a%20challenge%2C%20though%2C%20was%20dating%20with%20a%20disability.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20need%20to%20get%20more%20comfortable%20talking%20about%20the%20disabled%20experience%20as%20a%20whole%2C%20but%20particularly%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20dating%20and%20romance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20with%20disabilities%20want%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fablesplaining-nondisabled-partners-think-know-whats-best-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edate%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20have%20casual%20sex%2C%20and%20they%20deserve%20access%20to%20those%20needs%20like%20everyone%20else.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20stranger%20told%20me%20it%20would%20be%20selfish%20of%20me%20to%20have%20kids%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20five%20years%20I%20had%20bad%20experiences%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fdating-app-algorithms-hard-to-manipulate-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edating%20apps%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20experienced%20a%20lot%20of%20rejection%20and%20discrimination%20for%20being%20disabled%20and%2C%20because%20my%20disability%20is%20invisible%2C%20it%20was%20hard%20to%20know%20when%20to%20disclose%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETelling%20a%20non-disabled%20person%20I%20was%20dating%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eabout%20my%20disability%20was%20the%20worst%20because%20they%20often%20got%20freaked%20out%20and%20ran%20away.%20There%20were%20so%20many%20times%20when%20I%20would%20just%20bite%20my%20tongue%20and%20make%20up%20this%20whole%20other%20scenario%20in%20the%20conversation%20just%20so%20that%20I%20could%20avoid%20telling%20them%20I%20was%20disabled.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20preferred%20hiding%20my%20disability%20from%20people%20because%20I%20felt%20embarrassed%2C%20but%20sometimes%20that%20wasn't%20possible.%20One%20guy%20once%20asked%20me%20to%20go%20on%20a%20walk%20for%20a%20first%20date%2C%20but%20I%20was%20just%20recovering%20from%20surgery%20so%20I%20suggested%20a%20picnic%20instead.%20He%20asked%20me%20what%20I%20did%20to%20injure%20myself%2C%20and%20I%20told%20him%20that%20I%20had%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fmy-chronic-pain-was-caused-by-lupus-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econnective%20tissue%20disorder%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20told%20me%20it%20would%20be%20selfish%20for%20me%20to%20have%20biological%20children%20without%20even%20knowing%20if%20my%20illness%20is%20genetic.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAnd%20those%20kinds%20of%20comments%20were%20common.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20things%20like%20that%20happened%2C%20I%20would%20delete%20the%20app%20for%20six%20months.%20I%20always%20searched%20online%20for%20a%20disabled%20dating%20app%20or%20chronic%20illness%20dating%20app%2C%20but%20the%20few%20results%20were%20either%20full%20of%20bots%2C%20spammers%2C%20or%20people%20who%20fetishize%20disability.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20thought%2C%20%26quot%3BHow%20is%20there%20not%20an%20app%20for%20people%20like%20me%3F%26quot%3B%20but%20always%20ended%20up%20redownloading%20a%20mainstream%20dating%20app%20and%20starting%20the%20vicious%20cycle%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThrough%20therapy%2C%20I%20realized%20my%20beliefs%20were%20rooted%20in%20internalized%20ableism%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20past%2C%20I%20wasn't%20open%20to%20dating%20someone%20else%20with%20a%20chronic%20illness.%20I%20was%20ashamed%20of%20my%20disability%20because%20I%20was%20being%20told%20I%20was%20unworthy%2C%20which%20I%20believed%2C%20and%20then%20I%20put%20that%20bias%20on%20other%20people%20with%20disabilities.%20Through%20therapy%2C%20I%20was%20able%20to%20unpack%20that%20and%20realize%20it%20was%20rooted%20in%20internalized%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fpeople-with-disabilities-are-sharing-their-stories-with-abled-people-on-twitter-2019-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eableism%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20I%20think%20that%20having%20shared%20experiences%20is%20really%20important%20and%20I%20can%20find%20that%20in%20someone%20who%20has%20a%20chronic%20illness%20and%20similar%20life%20values.%20I'm%20not%20dating%20at%20the%20moment%20but%20I%20am%20hopeful%20and%20believe%20that%20I'll%20find%20my%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMy%20sister%20and%20I%20decided%20to%20make%20an%20app%20to%20help%20me%20find%20love%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20have%20a%20procedure%20that%20I%20had%20been%20putting%20off%20for%20a%20year%20because%20I%20was%20afraid%20of%20how%20it%20would%20change%20my%20social%20life.%20I%20got%20a%20feeding%20tube%20in%20my%20abdomen%2C%20which%20means%20I%20can%20no%20longer%20eat%20orally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%20I%20just%20thought%20there%20was%20no%20way%20these%20people%20I%20see%20on%20Bumble%20are%20going%20to%20accept%20me%20now%20if%20they%20hadn't%20accepted%20me%20already.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20told%20my%20older%20sister%20Alexa%2C%20who%20I%20live%20with%2C%20that%20I%20just%20wanted%20a%20place%20to%20meet%20people%20like%20me.%20Although%20she's%20not%20disabled%2C%20she's%20experienced%20secondhand%20discrimination%20on%20dates%20and%20had%20people%20make%20offensive%20comments%20about%20her%20genetics%20because%20both%20our%20dad%20and%20I%20are%20disabled.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20suggested%20that%20we%20make%20that%20place%20ourselves.%20It%20was%20an%20impulsive%20decision%20and%20we%20got%20cracking%20right%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20co-founded%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finfo.dateabilityapp.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDateability%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20the%20only%20free%20dating%20app%20for%20the%20disabled%20and%20chronically%20ill%20community%2C%20and%20launched%20on%20October%201%2C%202022.%20Currently%2C%20there%20are%20almost%2011%2C000%20users.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20makes%20dating%20a%20lot%20less%20fun%20when%20you're%20constantly%20worrying%20about%20when%20and%20how%20to%20disclose%20your%20disability%2C%20so%20I%20wanted%20to%20take%20that%20pressure%20off%20of%20users.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20we%20created%20a%20section%20called%20Dateability%20Deets%20where