%20that%20this%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhole-foods-black-lives-matter-constitutional-rights-violated-first-amendment-2022-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eviolated%20the%20company's%20dress%20code%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20generally%20told%20them%20that%20they%20could%20either%20remove%20the%20item%20in%20question%20or%20clock%20out%20and%20go%20home%20early%2C%20which%20incurred%20attendance%20or%20dress-policy%20violations%2C%20allegedly%20leading%20to%20discharges%20in%20some%20cases%2C%20per%20the%20case%20proceedings.%20Some%20employees%20staged%20walkouts%20after%20being%20told%20they%20couldn't%20wear%20accessories%20with%20BLM%20slogans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Whole%20Foods%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5f04a8db5af6cc2bda317e36%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221646%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEmployees%20sued%20Whole%20Foods%20for%20sending%20workers%20home%20for%20wearing%20BLM%20masks.%3Cp%3EErin%20Clark%2FThe%20Boston%20Globe%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20summary%20of%20the%20case%2C%20Ariel%20L.%20Sotolongo%2C%20an%20administrative%20law%20judge%20for%20the%20National%20Labor%20Relations%20Board%2C%20said%20that%20the%20grocery-store%20chain%20hadn't%20disputed%20that%20it%20had%20banned%20staff%20from%20wearing%20BLM%20messaging%20and%20disciplined%20them%20for%20violating%20this%20policy.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20the%20case%20focused%20on%20whether%20this%20ban%20broke%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nlrb.gov%2Fabout-nlrb%2Frights-we-protect%2Fwhats-law%2Femployers%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESection%207%20of%20the%20Labor%20Relations%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20says%20that%20the%20wearing%20of%20some%20items%20related%20to%20employment%20conditions%20like%20union%20buttons%20and%20T-shirts%20is%20a%20protected%20concerted%20activity%2C%20and%20whether%20disciplining%20staff%20based%20on%20this%20was%20unlawful%2C%20Sotolongo%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhole%20Foods'%20uniform%20policy%20had%20told%20staff%20that%20to%20wear%20company-branded%20shirts%20or%20ones%20%26quot%3Bwithout%20any%20visible%20slogan%2C%20message%2C%20logo%20or%20advertising%20on%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20said%20only%20company%20hats%20were%20allowed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBarbara%20Smith%2C%20the%20retailer's%20vice%20president%20of%20team%20member%20services%2C%20testified%20that%20after%20workers%20started%20wearing%20items%20with%20BLM%20messaging%2C%20the%20company's%20leadership%20agreed%20that%20this%20violated%20the%20dress%20code%20and%20discussed%20how%20to%20enforce%20the%20policy%20while%20acknowledging%20the%20delicacy%20of%20the%20subject%20and%20respecting%20staff's%20opinions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20NLRB%20General%20Counsel%2C%20representing%20the%20affected%20Whole%20Foods%20staff%2C%20argued%20that%20workers%20wore%20items%20with%20BLM%20messaging%20at%20work%20to%20show%20solidarity%20with%20their%20Black%20colleagues%20and%20show%20opposition%20to%20systemic%20racism%20in%20the%20workplace.%20The%20General%20Counsel%20also%20said%20that%20some%20employees%20saw%20Whole%20Foods'%20ban%20of%20BLM%20messaging%20as%20discriminatory%20and%20racist%2C%20and%20therefore%20their%20defiance%20of%20the%20policy%20was%20protected%20activity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Sotolongo%20wrote%20that%20interviews%20with%20workers%20suggested%20that%20the%20majority%20started%20donning%20BLM%20messaging%20to%20show%20support%20for%20the%20movement%20generally%2C%20without%20any%20specific%20goal%20connected%20to%20their%20employment%20or%20working%20conditions.%20Workers%20only%20started%20looking%20for%20a%20way%20to%20connect%20the%20items%20to%20their%20employment%20to%20provide%20legal%20cover%20after%20Whole%20Foods%20starting%20disciplining%20staff%20for%20violating%20the%20policy%2C%20Sotolongo%20wrote%2C%20citing%20online%20messages%20between%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESotolongo%20also%20wrote%20that%20the%20%26quot%3Bvast%20majority%26quot%3B%20of%20employees%20disciplined%20for%20wearing%20BLM%20messaging%20were%20not%20Black.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20fact%20that%20BLM%20may%20be%20a%20movement%20of%20great%20significance%20to%20African%20Americans%2C%20and%20that%20its%20goals%20are%20valid%2C%20does%20not%20mean%20that%20a%20rule%20prohibiting%20the%20displaying%20of%20such%20message%20at%20work%20is%20'racist%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20fact%20that%20WFM%20in%20the%20past%20had%20permitted%20and%20even%20supported%20employees%20donning%20messages%20is%20support%20other%20social-political%20causes%2C%20such%20as%20the%20LGTBQ%20movement%2C%20does%20not%20support%20the%20implication%20that%20the%20banning%20of%20BLM%20messaging%20was%20racially%20motivated.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESotolongo%20concluded%20in%20a%20decision%20on%20Wednesday%20that%20Whole%20Foods%20workers%20who%20wore%20items%20with%20slogans%20related%20to%20the%20BLM%20movement%20weren't%20engaged%20in%20protected%20activity%20under%20Section%207%20of%20the%20Act%20and%20that%20disciplinary%20actions%20taken%20by%20the%20retailer%2C%20including%20verbal%20and%20written%20warnings%2C%20didn't%20violate%20the%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Shannon%20Liss-Riordan%2C%20the%20lawyer%20representing%20the%20workers%2C%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F12%2F21%2Fbusiness%2Fwhole-foods-black-lives-matter.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20response%20to%20the%20ruling%20that%20if%20employers%20believed%20that%20they%20were%20taking%20an%20action%20to%20improve%20the%20terms%20and%20conditions%20of%20their%20workplace%2C%20that%20should%20count%20as%20protected%20activity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESotolongo%20did%2C%20however%2C%20note%20that%20the%20uniform%20policy%20Whole%20Foods%20had%20in%20place%20from%202013%20to%202020%20violated%20part%20of%20Section%208%20of%20the%20Act%20because%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Boverly%20broad%26quot%3B%20and%20didn't%20state%20that%20staff%20could%20wear%20union%20insignia.%20Barbara%20Smith%2C%20the%20retailer's%20vice%20president%20of%20team%20member%20services%2C%20had%20previously%20testified%20that%20the%20policy%20allowed%20workers%20to%20wear%20union%20insignia%20like%20pins%20and%20buttons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhole%20Foods%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fedition.cnn.com%2F2023%2F12%2F21%2Fbusiness%2Fwhole-foods-ban-black-lives-matter%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECNN%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Bpleased%26quot%3B%20with%20the%20outcome%2C%20adding%20that%20it%20was%20focused%20on%20creating%20%26quot%3Bboth%20a%20safe%20and%20inclusive%20workplace%20for%20all.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhole-foods-new-dress-code-policy-employee-reactions-2020-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWhole%20Foods%20updated%20its%20dress%20code%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20late%202020%2C%20which%20explicitly%20prohibited%20employees%20from%20wearing%20face%20masks%20with%20prints%2C%20slogans%2C%20or%20logos%20bigger%20than%20one%20inch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhole-foods-blm-pins-face-masks-punish-workers-discharge-discipline-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703249432000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F658579eaa79e5746976c95db%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhole-foods-blm-pins-face-masks-punish-workers-discharge-discipline-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20judge%20said%20that%20wearing%20these%20items%20wasn't%20a%20protected%20activity%20and%20Whole%20Foods%20could%20therefore%20discipline%20staff%20for%20violating%20its%20uniform%20policy.%22%2C%22author%22%3