6208332.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Why%20Didn't%20You%20Make%20Adjustments%3A%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20To%20States%20After%20Loss%20To%20BJP%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress's%20defeat%20in%20three%20important%20states%20just%20months%20before%20the%20national%20election%20weighed%20heavily%20in%20a%20meeting%20of%20the%20party's%20top%20leadership%20on%20Thursday%2C%20with%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20strongly%20emphasizing%20upon%20the%20need%20to%20accommodate%20regional%20parties%20in%20the%20fight%20against%20the%20BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20meeting%20of%20the%20Congress%20Working%20Committee%20(CWC)%20saw%20leaders%20from%20party%20chief%20Mallikarjun%20Kharge%20to%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20stressing%20on%20opposition%20unity%20to%20take%20on%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20and%20the%20BJP%20in%20the%202024%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20state%20elections%20were%20held%20up%20as%20an%20example%20of%20what%20not%20to%20do%2C%20especially%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20where%20the%20Congress%20failed%20to%20capitalise%20on%20four-term%20anti-incumbency.%20The%20Congress%20also%20lost%20power%20in%20Rajasthan%20and%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20managing%20a%20lone%20win%20in%20Telangana.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERahul%20Gandhi%2C%20say%20sources%2C%20questioned%20why%20state%20units%20were%20not%20ready%20to%20make%20adjustments%20with%20smaller%20parties%20to%20try%20and%20defeat%20the%20BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECongress%20veteran%20Kamal%20Nath%2C%20who%20led%20the%20party's%20flop%20campaign%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20came%20in%20for%20criticism%20though%20he%20was%20not%20present%20as%20he%20is%20not%20a%20CWC%20member.%20Several%20leaders%20called%20out%20what%20they%20described%20as%20his%20autocratic%20style%20and%20stubborn%20refusal%20to%20accept%20feedback%20or%20ideas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20party%20believes%20that%20the%20losses%20in%20the%20three%20states%20was%20mainly%20due%20to%20the%20BJP%20collecting%20votes%20that%20would%20have%20gone%20to%20smaller%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20apparent%20reference%20to%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20where%20Kamal%20Nath%20famously%20said%20%26quot%3BAkhilesh-wakhilesh%26quot%3B%20while%20dismissing%20talk%20of%20an%20alliance%20with%20Samajwadi%20Party%20leader%20Akhilesh%20Yadav%2C%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20said%20the%20Congress%20should%20have%20agreed%20to%20seat-sharing%20with%20smaller%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20cannot%20be%20termed%20as%20an%20intrusion%2C%20he%20articulated.%20The%20Congress%20needs%20to%20accommodate%20others%20and%20every%20percentage%20of%20vote%20matters%20in%20the%20fight%20against%20the%20BJP%2C%20said%20the%20MP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERahul%20Gandhi%20also%20felt%20that%20the%20party%20did%20not%20campaign%20properly%20in%20the%20three%20states%20and%20cited%20the%20example%20of%20Telangana%2C%20say%20sources%2C%20where%20the%20Congress%20made%20a%20remarkable%20comeback%20from%20third%20position%20just%20a%20year%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20some%20leaders%20sought%20to%20highlight%20the%20BJP's%20organisational%20strength%20in%20all%20three%20states%2C%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20is%20said%20to%20have%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20Congress%20did%20win%20all%20three%20in%202018%20and%20that%20the%20BJP%20is%20not%20unbeatable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMallikarjun%20Kharge%20reportedly%20endorsed%20the%20view%20and%20said%20giving%20up%20four%20or%20five%20seats%20should%20not%20have%20been%20an%20issue%20in%20the%20larger%20interests%20of%20the%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%20chief%2C%20who%20has%20been%20pitched%20as%20the%20prime%20ministerial%20face%20of%20the%20INDIA%20bloc%2C%20was%20said%20to%20have%20sent%20a%20loud%20and%20clear%20message%20to%20the%20party%20-%20lessons%20must%20be%20learnt%20from%20the%20state%20election%20verdict%20and%20the%20Congress%20has%20to%20fight%20unitedly%20with%20alliance%20partners%20of%20the%20INDIA%20bloc%20to%20take%20on%20the%20BJP-led%20NDA.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20point%20was%20reinforced%20in%20the%20CWC%20resolution%2C%20which%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BThis%20meeting%20of%20the%20CWC%20expresses%20its%20firmest%20resolve%20to%20be%20fully%20prepared%20at%20the%20earliest%20to%20fight%20the%20forthcoming%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%20both%20as%20a%20party%20in%20its%20own%20right%20and%20also%20as%20a%20member%20of%20the%20INDIA%20group.%20It%20reiterates%20the%20determination%20of%20the%20Indian%20National%20Congress%20to%20take%20all%20steps%20necessary%20to%20make%20the%20INDIA%20group%20an%20effective%20bulwark%20and%20force%20against%20the%20BJP%20and%20its%20allies.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703235540000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-12%2Fh9laa1a4_sonia-gandhi-mallikarjun-kharge-rahul-gandhi-twitter_625x300_22_December_23.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fwhy-didnt-you-make-adjustments-rahul-gandhi-to-states-after-loss-to-bjp-4721879%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Congress's%20defeat%20in%20three%20important%20states%20just%20months%20before%20the%20national%20election%20weighed%20heavily%20in%20a%20meeting%20of%20the%20party's%20top%20leadership%20on%20Thursday%2C%20with%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20strongly%20emphasizing%20upon%20the%20need%20to%20accommodate%20regional%20parties.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fwhy-didnt-you-make-adjustments-rahul-gandhi-to-states-after-loss-to-bjp-4721879%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fwhy-didnt-you-make-adjustments-rahul-gandhi-to-states-after-loss-to-bjp-4721879%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fwhy-didnt-you-make-adjustments-rahul-gandhi-to-states-after-loss-to-bjp-4721879%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Odisha%20Congress%20Leaders%20Hopeful%20of%20Revival%2C%20but%20Is%20It%20Realistic%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F10%2F18143119%2FSIRSA-GENERAL-PICS.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBhubaneswar%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Congress%2C%20which%20has%20been%20out%20of%20power%20in%20Odisha%20for%20the%20last%2023%20years%2C%20is%20looking%20to%20revive%20its%20fortunes%20in%20the%20state%20in%20the%202024%20elections.%20State%20party%20leaders%2C%20who%20had%20a%20meeting%20with%20AICC%20president%20Mallikarjun%20Kharge%2C%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20and%20other%20senior%20leaders%20in%20Delhi%20on%20Wednesday%20to%20discuss%20the%20strategy%20for%20the%20coming%20polls%2C%20appear%20upbeat%20about%20its%20prospects.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMost%20of%20the%20senior%20state%20leaders%20including%20Pradesh%20Congress%20Committee%20(PCC)%20president%20Sarat%20Pattnayak%20were%20present%20at%20the%20meeting.%20The%20AICC%20president%20was%20optimistic%20about%20our%20prospects%20in%20the%20state%20and%20said%20that%20Odisha%20will%20be%20in%20focus%20in%20the%20next%20elections%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20former%20PCC%20president%20Jaydev%20Jena%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20party%20has%20no%20dearth%20of%20issues%20against%20the%20Naveen%20Patnaik-led%20Biju%20Janata%20Dal%20(BJD).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CCorruption%2C%20unemployment%2C%20and%20complete%20lack%20of%20progress%20on%20any%20front%20remain%20major%20issues.%20We%20are%20also%20going%20to%20highlight%20the%20helplessness%20of%20chief%20minister%20Naveen%20Patnaik%20who%20seems%20to%20be%20a%20puppet%20in%20the%20hands%20of%20bureaucrat-turned-politician%20V.K.%20Pandian.%20We%20will%20also%20tell%20people%20that%20the%20BJD%20and%20BJP%20are%20two%20sides%20of%20the%20same%20coin%2C%E2%80%9D%20continued%20Jena%2C%20who%20thinks%20that%20the%20Congress%20which%20has%20been%20going%20through%20a%20bad%20phase%20in%20Odisha%20stands%20a%20good%20chance%20this%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETalking%20to%20media%20persons%20after%20the%20meeting%20with%20AICC%20bigwigs%20in%20Delhi%2C%20Sarat%20Pattnayak%20said%20that%20the%20party%20would%20step%20up%20its%20fight%20against%20the%20BJD%20and%20BJP%2C%20which%20he%20said%20are%20equally%20corrupt.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20discussed%20the%20strategy%20for%202024.%20The%20biggest%20issue%20against%20the%20state%20government%20is%20corruption%20and%20the%20number%20of%20scams%20that%20are%20taking%20place%2C%E2%80%9D%20averred%20Pattnayak.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20senior%20party%20leaders%2C%20including%20general%20secretary%20and%20former%20MLA%20Lalatendu%20Mohapatra%2C%20also%20exuded%20confidence%20about%20the%20party%20doing%20better%20in%20the%20coming%20elections%20compared%20to%20the%20past.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20better%20prepared%20this%20time%20and%20the%20strategic%20meeting%20held%20in%20Delhi%20is%20going%20to%20help%20us%20a%20lot.%20The%20most%20important%20thing%20is%20that%20people%20of%20the%20state%20now%20know%20that%20BJP%20and%20BJD%20are%20having%20a%20fixed%20bout%20in%20Odisha.%20They%20are%20going%20to%20reject%20both%20of%20them%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Mohapatra.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20notwithstanding%20the%20optimism%20of%20state%20Congress%20leaders%2C%20things%20are%20not%20going%20to%20be%20easy%20for%20the%20party%20if%20its%20record%20in%20the%20state%20is%20anything%20to%20go%20by.%20Plagued%20by%20factional%20feuds%2C%20the%20fortunes%20of%20the%20party%20have%20been%20declining%20consistently%20in%20Odisha%20since%202000%2C%20when%20it%20was%20thrown%20out%20of%20power%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20a%20disastrous%20super-cyclone%20that%20generated%20a%20wave%20of%20public%20anger.%20A%20BJD-BJP%20coalition%20government%20led%20by%20Naveen%20Patnaik%20came%20to%20power%20in%202000%20and%20even%20though%20the%20coalition%20collapsed%20in%202009%2C%20with%20the%20BJP%20pulling%20out%2C%20Patnaik%20remains%20in%20charge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06172238%2FF41ji1pXIAAYZbB.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06172238%2FF41ji1pXIAAYZbB.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06172238%2FF41ji1pXIAAYZbB-300x153.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06172238%2FF41ji1pXIAAYZbB-1024x523.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-678686%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22613%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EOdisha%20chief%20minister%20Naveen%20Patnaik.%20Photo%3A%20X%20(Twitter)%2F%40Naveen_Odisha%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20BJD%20won%20103%20assembly%20and%2014%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%20in%20the%20simultaneously%20held%20polls%20in%202009%2C%20the%20Congress%20could%20manage%2027%20assembly%20and%20six%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%20in%20those%20elections.%20The%20BJP%20was%20reduced%20to%20a%20single-digit%20(6)%20figure%20in%20the%20147-strong%20state%20assembly.%20It%20failed%20to%20win%20even%20a%20single%20Lok%20Sabha%20seat%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20in%20the%202014%20elections%2C%20the%20vote%20share%20of%20the%20Congress%20in%20Odisha%E2%80%99s%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%20nosedived%20to%2026%25%20from%2032.75%25%20in%202009.%20The%20party%20won%2016%20seats%20in%20the%20state%20assembly%20but%20could%20not%20open%20its%20account%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%20In%20sharp%20contrast%2C%20the%20Naveen%20Patnaik-led%20BJD%20swept%20the%20polls%20%E2%80%93%20grabbing%2020%20of%20the%2021%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%20and%20117%20seats%20in%20the%20state%20assembly.%20The%20BJP%20won%2010%20assembly%20seats%20and%20the%20Sundergarh%20Lok%20Sabha%20seat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECongress%20hit%20rock%20bottom%20in%20the%202019%20elections%2C%20when%20it%20won%20just%20nine%20seats%20in%20the%20state%20assembly%2C%20losing%20the%20tag%20of%20the%20main%20opposition%20party%20to%20the%20BJP%20%E2%80%93%20which%20bagged%2023%20seats.%20In%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20the%20Congress%20had%20a%20consolation%20victory%20in%20Koraput%2C%20where%20its%20candidate%20scraped%20through%20by%20a%20narrow%20margin.%20The%20main%20beneficiary%20of%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20plummeting%20fortunes%20in%20Odisha%20has%20been%20the%20BJP%2C%20which%20not%20only%20emerged%20as%20the%20main%20opposition%20party.%20Its%20Lok%20Sabha%20tally%20went%20from%201%20to%208%20in%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20initial%20days%20of%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20slide%20in%20the%20state%2C%20the%20party%20which%20gained%20most%20was%20the%20BJD.%20But%20as%20its%20decline%20became%20more%20acute%2C%20it%20was%20the%20BJP%20which%20started%20benefitting.%20Erstwhile%20Congress%20loyalists%20transferred%20their%20votes%20to%20the%20party.%20In%20the%20latest%20phase%20which%20began%20in%202019%2C%20the%20Congress%20was%20near%20decimation%20in%20the%20state.%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20see%20any%20chance%20of%20its%20revival.%20The%20BJP%20will%20gain%20from%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20fall%20and%20the%20anti-incumbency%20factor%20which%20is%20going%20to%20hit%20the%20Naveen%20Patnaik%20government%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20state%20BJP%20general%20secretary%20Bhrigu%20Buxipatra.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20panchayat%20elections%20held%20in%20the%20state%20in%202017%2C%20the%20BJP%20had%20made%20major%20gains%20with%20its%20zila%20parishad%20tally%20going%20up%20to%20297%20from%2036%20in%202012%2C%20mainly%20because%20of%20a%20sharp%20decline%20in%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20popularity%20%E2%80%93%20its%20total%20zila%20parishad%20seats%20came%20down%20to%2060%20from%20126.%20However%2C%20in%20the%202022%20rural%20polls%2C%20when%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20ZP%20tally%20went%20down%20further%20to%2037%2C%20it%20was%20the%20BJD%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fodishas-panchayat-poll-outcome-seals-naveen-patnaiks-invincibility%5C%22%3Egained%20the%20most%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20claiming%20a%20record%20number%20of%20766%20zila%20parishad%20seats.%20The%20BJP%20also%20suffered%20a%20massive%20jolt%2C%20getting%20reduced%20to%2042%20ZP%20seats%20from%20297.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20sharp%20decline%20in%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20fortunes%20in%20Odisha%20can%20be%20directly%20attributed%20to%20the%20internal%20feuds%2C%20which%20have%20prevented%20it%20from%20presenting%20a%20united%20face%20in%20the%20elections.%20Most%20of%20the%20PCC%20presidents%20have%20had%20to%20struggle%20with%20this%20problem%20and%20Sarat%20Pattnayak%2C%20who%20took%20over%20from%20Niranjan%20Patnaik%20in%20May%20last%20year%2C%20is%20no%20exception.%20His%20running%20feud%20with%20senior%20party%20leaders%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fbhubaneswar%2Fcongress-suspends-moquim-and-biswal%2Farticleshow%2F101793485.cms%23%5C%22%3EChiranjib%20Biswal%20and%20Mohammed%20Moquim%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20MLA%20from%20Barabati-Cuttack%2C%20has%20been%20the%20talk%20of%20party%20circles.%20Both%20the%20leaders%20were%20suspended%20by%20him%20a%20few%20months%20ago%20on%20the%20charges%20of%20indulging%20in%20anti-party%20activities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20Niranjan%20Patnaik%E2%80%99s%20term%2C%20on%20the%20eve%20of%20the%202019%20elections%2C%20he%20faced%20a%20virtual%20revolt%20when%20then%20state%20party%20working%20president%2C%20Naba%20Kishore%20Das%2C%20who%20was%20an%20MLA%20from%20Jharsuguda%2C%20quit%20the%20party%20along%20with%20his%20colleague%20from%20Sundergarh%20Jogesh%20Singh.%20Das%20won%20the%20election%20on%20a%20BJD%20ticket%20and%20became%20a%20minister%20in%20the%20Naveen%20Patnaik%20government.%20He%20was%20assassinated%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fodisha-minister-n