3E%20of%202023%2C%20and%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.meity.gov.in%2Fwritereaddata%2Ffiles%2FDigital%2520Personal%2520Data%2520Protection%2520Act%25202023.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EDigital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Act%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%202023.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Lok%20Sabha%20passed%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%20on%20December%2020%20and%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20on%20December%2021%2C%20and%20it%20will%20become%20an%20Act%20after%20the%20President%E2%80%99s%20assent.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EAnything%20can%20be%20censored%20under%20the%20new%20Broadcasting%20Bill%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20legislation%20aimed%20at%20regulating%20online%20content%2C%20including%20news%2C%20were%20%E2%80%9Cextremely%20broad%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cvague%E2%80%9D%2C%20said%20Ritu%20Kapur%2C%20CEO%20and%20co-founder%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Quint%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20There%20is%20currently%20a%20%E2%80%9Ccomplete%20lack%20of%20clarity%E2%80%9D%20on%20what%20can%20lead%20to%20a%20punishment%2C%20interception%2C%20investigation%2C%20inquiry%2C%20or%20censorship%2C%20said%20Kapur.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShe%20said%20the%20provision%20for%20content%20evaluation%20committees%20(CECs)%20in%20the%20draft%20broadcasting%20bill%2C%20asking%20broadcasters%20to%20broadcast%20only%20those%20programmes%20self-certified%20through%20these%20CECs%2C%20would%20be%20difficult%20for%20news%20media%20to%20follow.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20a%20reason%20news%20organisations%20have%20editors%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Kapoor.%20%E2%80%9CWhy%20do%20we%20need%20this%20content%20evaluation%20committee%3F%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDigital%20news%20content%20creator%20Meghnad%20S%20spoke%20about%20how%20the%20difference%20between%20journalists%20and%20content%20creators%20has%20been%20blurred%20in%20recent%20legislation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMeghnad%20said%20anyone%20making%20social%20commentary%20online%20%E2%80%93%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eincluding%20comedians%2C%20Instagram%20meme%20pages%2C%20even%20those%20running%20WhatsApp%20communities%20%E2%80%93%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ecould%20face%20the%20same%20restrictions%20proposed%20for%20news%20media%20in%20the%20Broadcasting%20Bill.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20was%20referring%20to%20the%20broad%20definition%20of%20%E2%80%9Cnews%20and%20current%20affairs%20programmes%E2%80%9D%20prescribed%20in%20the%20draft%20of%20the%20Bill%2C%20which%20requires%20such%20programmes%20to%20adhere%20to%20advertising%20and%20programme%20codes%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mib.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fpc1_0.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eprescribed%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20by%20the%20government.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMeghnad%20said%20these%20codes%20restricted%20programming%20for%20a%20variety%20of%20supposed%20transgressions%2C%20such%20as%20%E2%80%9Csnobbish%20behaviour%20(%E2%80%A6)%2C%20decency%2C%20public%20morality%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20unclear%20if%20the%20government%20will%20continue%20with%20the%20existing%20codes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMeghnad%20expressed%20concern%20over%20the%20requirement%20of%20verifiable%20biometric-based%20identification%20for%20users%20of%20telecom%20services%20in%20the%20telecom%20bill.%20For%20journalists%2C%20he%20said%2C%20this%20could%20mean%20that%20their%20sources%20can%20no%20longer%20be%20anonymous%20when%20they%20share%20news.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMeena%20Kotwal%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20the%20news%20website%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Mooknayak%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20said%20these%20laws%20could%20be%20used%20for%20%E2%80%9Cselective%20targeting%E2%80%9D%20of%20people%20speaking%20on%20issues%20that%20the%20government%20did%20not%20want%20to%20discuss.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcontrol-all-or-delete-the-draft-broadcast-bill-is-a-blueprint-for-censorship%5C%22%3EControl%20%2B%20All%20or%20Delete%3A%20The%20Draft%20Broadcast%20Bill%20Is%20a%20Blueprint%20for%20Censorship%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShe%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CSince%20things%20are%20in%20the%20hands%20of%20the%20government%2C%20it%20can%20decide%20what%20is%20right%20or%20wrong.%20There%20are%20a%20lot%20of%20ministers%20in%20the%20government%20who%20put%20out%20wrong%20information%2C%20but%20no%20one%20will%20target%20them.%20And%20even%20if%20our%20information%20is%20correct%2C%20it%20is%20very%20easy%20to%20target%20us%E2%80%9D.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAslah%20Kayyalakkath%2C%20the%20founding%20editor%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EMaktoob%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20shared%20his%20experience%20of%20how%20he%20landed%20in%20trouble%20with%20the%20Kerala%20police%20because%20of%20a%2030%20October%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmaktoobmedia.com%2Findia%2Fin-kerala-muslim-youths-detained-for-hours-following-blast-accuse-kerala-police-of-anti-muslim-bias%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Estory%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20by%20a%20freelance%20journalist%20alleging%20anti-Muslim%20bias%20by%20the%20Kerala%20police.%20The%20police%20filed%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thenewsminute.com%2Fkerala%2Ffir-against-kerala-journo-for-report-on-allegations-of-anti-muslim-bias-by-police%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Efirst%20information%20report%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(FIR)%20against%20the%20freelancer%2C%20and%20his%20phone%20was%20seized.%20Kayyalakkath%20was%20made%20a%20potential%20accused%20in%20the%20FIR%20and%20interrogated%20for%20several%20hours.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESeveral%20such%20instances%20of%20harassment%20and%20arrests%20of%20journalists%20publishing%20stories%20critical%20of%20the%20government%20and%20its%20institutions%20have%20been%20recorded%20in%20the%20past%20few%20years.%20This%20not%20only%20discourages%20journalists%20but%20also%20instils%20a%20feeling%20of%20fear%20that%20leads%20to%20self-censorship.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cb%3ESurveillance%20and%20privacy%20concerns%20in%20Telecom%20Bill%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAdvocate%20Apar%20Gupta%20said%20there%20were%20major%20concerns%20related%20to%20surveillance%20and%20interception%2C%20internet%20shutdowns%2C%20encrypted%20services%2C%20and%20duties%20of%20users%20in%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202023%20(which%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Finternetfreedom%2Fstatus%2F1737454002198262255%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Epassed%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20with%2095%20of%20its%20MPs%20suspended)%2C%20in%20a%20political%20economy%20%E2%80%9Cwhere%20there%20is%20a%20growth%E2%80%9D%20of%20chosen%20companies%20and%20increased%20government%20control.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EReferring%20to%20internet%20shutdowns%2C%20Gupta%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CLong%20periods%20of%20Internet%20shutdowns%20have%20caused%20grave%20amounts%20of%20economic%20and%20social%20injury%20to%20people%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20and%20Manipur%2C%20almost%20reducing%20them%20to%20a%20barbaric%20sort%20of%20existence%20during%20Covid%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20department%20of%20telecommunications%20still%20refuses%20to%20make%20a%20centralised%20repository%20of%20internet%20shutdowns%2C%20thereby%20reducing%20transparency%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Gupta.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20completely%20ignoring%20the%20central%20core%20of%20telecommunication%20rules%20that%20are%20required.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EGupta%20said%20the%20interception%20provisions%20in%20the%20new%20bill%20were%20worse%20than%20those%20in%20a%20previous%202022%20avatar%2C%20which%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ewas%20released%20for%20public%20consultation%20in%20September%20of%20that%20year.%20The%20department%20of%20telecommunications%20did%20not%20release%20the%20comments%20that%20were%20made.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20new%20Telecom%20Bill%20states%20that%20the%20Union%20government%20can%20ask%20for%20messages%20to%20be%20disclosed%20in%20an%20%E2%80%9Cintelligible%20format%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWhat%20that%20means%20is%20that%20if%20there%20is%20an%20interception%20order%2C%20and%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20WhatsApp%20message%20given%20to%20WhatsApp%2C%20%5Bthen%5D%20WhatsApp%20needs%20to%20decrypt%20it%20and%20give%20it%20to%20a%20law%20enforcement%20officer%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Gupta.%20%E2%80%9CAnd%20how%20will%20it%20do%20it%20if%20it%E2%80%99s%20implementing%20end-to-end%20encryption%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EWhatsApp%20currently%20claims%20to%20provide%20end-to-end%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffaq.whatsapp.com%2F820124435853543%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eencrypted%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20messaging%20services%2C%20which%20means%20that%20no%20one%20except%20those%20communicating%20with%20each%20other%20can%20read%20the%20messages%20being%20exchanged%2C%20not%20even%20WhatsApp.%20Asking%20WhatsApp%20to%20decrypt%20its%20messages%20could%20affect%20the%20privacy%20rights%20of%20Indians.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20hope%20is%20always%20obviously%20if%20you%E2%80%99re%20coming%20out%20with%20a%20new%20law%2C%20you%20would%20want%20policy%20to%20improve%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Gupta.%20%E2%80%9CYou%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20want%20it%20to%20just%20replicate%20the%20existing%20provisions.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAdvocate%20Vrinda%20Bhandari%20spoke%20about%20how%20search-and-seizure%20powers%20granted%20under%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%20were%20of%20concern.%20The%20bill%20allows%20any%20officer%20authorised%20by%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20search%20any%20place%20where%20%E2%80%9Cunauthorised%E2%80%9D%20telecom%20equipment%20is%20kept%20and%20seize%20it%2C%20or%2C%20for%20certain%20offences%2C%20such%20as%20unlawful%20interception%20and%20%E2%80%9Ccausing%20damage%20to%20telecommunication%20network%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBhandari%20said%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20powers%20under%20the%20bill%20were%20%E2%80%9Cvery%20broadly%20defined%E2%80%9D%20and%20provided%20no%20safeguards%20against%20interception.%20The%20new%20Bill%20would%20allow%20any%20social%20media%20messages%20on%20Manipur%20violence%20to%20be%20blocked%20for%20%E2%80%9Cinflaming%20tensions%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20added.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Bill%20allows%20the%20central%20government%20to%20intercept%20messages%20communicated%20via%20%E2%80%9Cany%20telecommunication%20equipment%E2%80%9D%20for%20reasons%20like%20%E2%80%9Cpublic%20emergency%20or%20in%20the%20interest%20of%20public%20safety%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnother%20controversial%20aspect%20of%20the%20Bill%20is%20the%20definition%20of%20%E2%80%9Ctelecommunication%20services%E2%80%9D.%20Bhandari%20argued%20that%20the%20current%20definition%20is%20still%20very%20broad%20and%20has%20the%20scope%20to%20include%20%E2%80%9Cany%20content%E2%80%9D%20under%20its%20ambit.%20This%20could%20cover%20services%20like%20WhatsApp%2C%20PayTm%20and%20Google%20Pay%2C%20she%20added.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIncluding%20internet-based%20services%20in%20the%20definition%20of%20%E2%80%9Ctelecommunication%20services%E2%80%9D%20would%20make%20them%20vulnerable%20to%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20power%20to%20restrict%20and%20suspend%20their%20services.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftech%2Ftelecommunications-bill-lays-the-ground-for-totalitarian-control-of-the-internet%5C%22%3ETelecommunications%20Bill%20Lays%20the%20Ground%20for%20Totalitarian%20Control%20of%20the%20Internet%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAdvocate%20Shreya%20Singhal%20said%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%20allowed%20all%20telecom%20services%20to%20be%20suspended%20for%20any%20%E2%80%9Cpublic%20emergency%E2%80%9D.%20The%20government%20would%20have%20the%20power%20to%20ban%20not%20only%20the%20internet%20but%20also%20mobile%20services.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ECensorship%20powers%20of%20the%20Broadcasting%20Bill%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EJournalist%20Anna%20M.M.%20Vetticad%20referred%20to%20growing%20self-censorship%20in%20the%20Hindi%20entertainment%20industry%2C%20describing%20it%20as%20%E2%80%9Cmind-boggling%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20an%20actor%20is%20outspoken%2C%20they%20will%20not%20cast%20that%20person%E2%80%9D%20because%20there%E2%80%99s%20potential%20for%20controversy%2C%20said%20Vetticad.%20Self-censorship%20was%20evident%20even%20with%20script-writers%20and%20financiers%2C%20she%20added.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EVetticad%20discussed%20the%20film%20%E2%80%9CBheed%2C%E2%80%9D%20which%20draws%20connections%20between%20the%20Covid%20crisis%20and%20India%E2%80%99s%201947%20partition.%20When%20the%20film%E2%80%99s%20director%2C%20Anubhav%20Sinha%2C%20ran%20into%20trouble%20with%20the%20censor%20board%2C%20the%20producer%20distanced%20himself%20from%20the%20project%20and%20had%20his%20own%20name%20removed%20from%20the%20credits%2C%20Vetticad%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CMultiple%20filmmakers%20have%20told%20me%20that%20the%20scripts%20of%20their%20shows%20and%20their%20films%20are%20being%20looked%20at%20for%20%5Bto%20check%20if%5D%20there%E2%80%99s%20anything%20that%20would%20offend%20the%20government%20%5Bor%20if%20there%5D%20is%20there%20anything%20that%20would%20offend%20Hindutva%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Vetticad.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShe%20also%20raised%20concerns%20with%20the%20provisions%20for%20content%20evaluation%20committees%20(CECs)%20in%20the%20broadcasting%20bill.%20The%20bill%20requires%20broadcasters%20to%20self-certify%20content%20before%20publication.%20The%20CEC%2C%20she%20said%2C%20would%20be%20another%20layer%20above%20existing%20censorship.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20broadcasting%20bill%20seeks%20to%20regulate%20broadcasting%20services%20over%20television%2C%20internet%2C%20and%20radio%2C%20allowing%20the%20government%20to%20regulate%20or%20censor%20content.%20The%20bill%20empowers%20the%20union%20government%20to%20delete%20or%20modify%20programmes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELawyer%20Alok%20Prasanna%2C%20co-founder%20and%20lead%20of%20Vidhi%20Centre%20for%20Legal%20Policy%2C%20Karnataka%2C%20described%20the%20broadcasting%20bill%20as%20a%20completely%20%E2%80%9Cconfused%20approach%E2%80%9D%20to%20regulating%20OTTs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAbhinandan%20Sekhri%2C%20co-founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ENewslaundry%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%C2%A0%20said%20it%20was%20important%20to%20remember%20that%20government%20regulations%20also%20applied%20to%20the%20media.%20%E2%80%9CI%20myself%20have%20faced%20in%20court%20in%20five%20different%20cases%2C%20three%20against%20income%20tax%20authorities%2C%20one%20against%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Times%20of%20India%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20one%20against%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%20Today%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EVibodh%20Parthasarathi%2C%20associate%20professor%20Jamia%20Millia%20Islamia%2C%20said%20that%20the%20broadcast%20regulations%20have%20been%20%E2%80%9Cunclear%E2%80%9D%20in%20finding%20the%20%E2%80%9Cobject%20of%20regulation%E2%80%9D.%20For%20instance%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20see%20a%20lack%20of%20state%20capacity%20in%20stipulating%20the%20methodology%20for%20audience%20measurement%E2%80%9D%2C%20a%20task%20that%20falls%20under%20the%20ambit%20of%20the%20central%20government%20under%20the%20broadcasting%20bill.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3EAkshit%20Chawla%20is%20an%20independent%20journalist%20based%20in%20New%20Delhi.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703227037000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F19122440%2FIMG_2179-e1703225994746.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Ftelecom-broadcasting-data-protection-bill-digipub%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22These%20legislations%20come%20at%20a%20time%20when%20journalists%20and%20filmmakers%20face%20greater%20pressure%20than%20ever%20to%20conform%20to%20government%20narratives%2C%20said%20experts%20at%20a%20Digipub%20conference.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Ftelecom-broadcasting-data-protection-bill-digipub%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22SBI%20to%20sign%20%24165%20million%20LoC%20with%20World%20Bank%20for%20rooftop%20solar%20projects%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703226846000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-05%2F19%2F