20a%20permanent%20basis.%20The%20scheme%20was%20recently%20in%20the%20news%20after%20former%20Army%20chief%20M.M.%20Naravane%20revealed%20in%20his%20forthcoming%20memoirs%20that%20the%20scheme%20was%20a%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fagnipath-scheme-bolt-out-of-the-blue-navy-air-force-former-army-chief-naravane-memoirs%5C%22%3Ebolt%20out%20of%20the%20blue%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20for%20the%20Navy%20and%20the%20Air%20Force.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Parliamentary%20Committee%20on%20Defence%2C%20which%20tabled%20a%20report%20in%20parliament%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20said%20that%20the%20nodal%20agency%20is%20required%20to%20provide%20employment%20and%20resettlement%20opportunities%20to%20Agniveers%20who%20are%20discharged%20after%20their%20four%20years%20of%20service.%20These%20Agniveers%20will%20have%20a%20much%20younger%20age%20profile%20compared%20to%20the%20ex-servicemen%20whose%20affairs%20are%20looked%20after%20by%20the%20Directorate%20General%20Resettlement%20(DGR).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tribuneindia.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Fparl-panel-for-setting-up-nodal-agency-to-help-ex-agniveers-574232%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Tribune%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20committee%20recommended%20that%20the%20DGR%20needs%20to%20%E2%80%9Cdevise%20a%20focused%20and%20special%20approach%20for%20re-settlement%20of%20such%20Agniveers%E2%80%9D.%20Educational%20and%20resettlement%20opportunities%20should%20be%20provided%20to%20them%2C%20the%20committee%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20noted%20that%20the%20re-employment%20of%20ex-servicemen%20through%20reserved%20posts%20in%20the%20police%20and%20elsewhere%2C%20which%20the%20MoD%20said%20was%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20satisfactory%E2%80%9D.%20According%20to%20The%20Tribune%2C%20the%C2%A0committee%20said%20a%20%E2%80%9Cdraft%20roster%20for%20ex-servicemen%E2%80%9D%20should%20be%20finalised%20and%20added%20that%20the%20MoD%20must%20pursue%20the%20Union%20and%20state%20governments%20should%20fill%20these%20reserved%20posts.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703226560000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F12152105%2FFmIKfgPaEAElGi9.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fparliamentary-panel-nodal-agency-resettlement-released-agniveers%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20released%20Agniveers%20will%20have%20a%20much%20younger%20age%20profile%20compared%20to%20the%20ex-servicemen%20whose%20affairs%20are%20looked%20after%20by%20the%20Directorate%20General%20Resettlement.%20A%20focused%20and%20special%20approach%20is%20needed%2C%20the%20committee%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fparliamentary-panel-nodal-agency-resettlement-released-agniveers%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22France%20split%20over%20environmental%20effects%20of%20Christmas%20trees%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703225197000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F03F4%2Fproduction%2F_132121010_chritmastreemonoculture_morvan1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-67781387%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20majority%20of%20the%20Christmas%20tree%20plantations%20in%20Burgundy%20rely%20on%20the%20use%20of%20chemical%20treatments.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A62%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-67781387%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-67781387.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-67781387.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22With%20Cleverly%20Drafted%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%20Government%20Tightens%20Grip%20on%20Digital%20India%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F14083515%2FUntitled-design-11.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Telecommunications%20Bill%2C%202023%2C%20passed%20by%20both%20houses%20of%20parliament%2C%20is%20another%20action%20to%20cement%20authoritarian%20control%20over%20the%20rights%20of%20ordinary%20citizens.%20Its%20impact%20will%20be%20felt%20directly%20in%20four%20clear%20ways.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20there%20is%20a%20clear%20power%20for%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20regulate%20and%20license%20OTT%20services%20such%20as%20WhatsApp%2C%20Signal%2C%20Gmail%20etc.%20Here%2C%20the%20unfounded%20hope%20and%20the%20underserved%20servility%20in%20statements%20that%20OTT%20regulation%20is%20excluded%20from%20the%20ambit%20of%20regulation%20of%20the%20Telecommunications%20Bill%2C%202023%2C%20is%20not%20borne%20out%20from%20its%20text.%20The%20Union%20government%20may%20prescribe%20licence%20conditions%20that%20may%20vary%20as%20per%20%E2%80%9Ctelecommunication%20service%E2%80%9D%20%5BSection%203(1)(a)%20and%20Section%203(1)(b)%5D%20and%20require%20prior%20registration%20that%20may%20be%20used%20for%20the%20government%20to%20weaken%20privacy%20and%20increase%20snooping%20in%20future.%20While%20the%20phrases%20%E2%80%9COTT%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9CMessaging%20Services%E2%80%9D%20or%20even%20%E2%80%9CEmail%E2%80%9D%20are%20not%20expressly%20mentioned%20in%20the%20Telecommunications%20Bill%20as%20in%20the%20draft%20version%2C%20they%20at%20the%20same%20time%20have%20not%20been%20expressly%20excluded%20from%20the%20definition%20of%20%E2%80%9Ctelecommunication%20service%E2%80%9D%20which%20means%2C%20%E2%80%9Cany%20service%20for%20telecommunication%E2%80%9D%20%5BSection%202(t)%5D.%20Further%2C%20the%20phrase%2C%20%E2%80%9Ctelecommunication%E2%80%9D%20is%20defined%20to%20include%2C%20%E2%80%9Ctransmission%E2%80%A6%20or%20reception%20of%20any%20messages%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%20Hence%2C%20internet-based%20messaging%20and%20email%20services%20are%20%3Cem%3Eincluded%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20the%20Telecommunications%20Bill%2C%202023%20extends%20colonial%20powers%20of%20interception%20of%20your%20communications%20without%20any%20safeguards.%20This%20is%20first%20done%20through%20powers%20to%20notify%20standards%20and%20conformity%20assessments%20that%20will%20include%20encryption%20%5BSection%2019(f)%5D.%20This%20may%20even%20be%20under%20grounds%20of%20national%20security%20%5BSection%2021%5D.%20Encryption%20is%20a%20technology%20that%20is%20used%20in%20internet-based%20messaging%20to%20ensure%20that%20only%20the%20sender%20and%20receiver%20read%20the%20message%20in%20plain%20text.%20Any%20person%20snooping%20in%20on%20the%20message%20during%20transmission%20cannot%20read%20it.%20However%2C%20standard%20setting%20powers%20may%20be%20used%20to%20create%20backdoors%2C%20introduce%20message%20traceability%20(identifying%20the%20author%20of%20a%20message)%2C%20or%20to%20create%20block%20lists%20of%20words%20(as%20is%20done%20in%20China%20on%20WeChat).%20This%20becomes%20clearer%20when%20you%20look%20at%20the%20powers%20of%20interception%20that%20require%20intercepted%20messages%20to%20be%20disclosed%20in%20an%20%E2%80%9Cintelligible%20format%E2%80%9D%20%5BSection%2020(2)%5D.%20There%20are%20no%20procedures%20and%20safeguards%20in%20the%20text%20of%20the%20law%20and%20the%20existing%20procedure%20under%20Rule%20419-A%20of%20the%20Telegraph%20Act%2C%20that%20has%20been%20abused%2C%20will%20continue%20%5BSection%2061%5D.%20For%20instance%2C%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20even%20now%20refuses%20to%20provide%20aggregate%20data%20on%20the%20number%20of%20interception%20orders%20that%20it%20issues.%20It%20is%20a%20completely%20unaccountable%20and%20secretive%20system%20of%20surveillance%20without%20any%20oversight%20by%20courts%20or%20Parliament%2C%20that%20is%20being%20made%20more%20severe%20without%20any%20reform.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20those%20stating%20that%20the%20present%20Telecommunications%20Bill%2C%202023%20contains%20exemptions%20for%20%E2%80%9Cpress%20messages%E2%80%9D%2C%20I%20encourage%20you%20to%20read%20more%20carefully.%20While%20it%20does%20create%20a%20sub-classification%20for%20%E2%80%9Ccorrespondents%20accredited%20with%20the%20Central%20or%20State%20Government%E2%80%9D%2C%20it%20does%20not%20offer%20any%20heightened%20protection%20(such%20as%20an%20additional%20procedural%20safeguard%20or%20reason)%20for%20the%20same%20conditions%20%5BSection%2020(3)%5D.%20There%20is%20also%20no%20%3Cem%3Enon%20obstante%3C%2Fem%3E%20clause%2C%20hence%20this%20does%20not%20override%20any%20other%20provision%20under%20any%20other%20law.%20Hence%2C%20it%20is%20merely%20clever%20drafting%2C%20for%20it%20reverts%20to%20the%20same%20process%20for%20interception%20as%20it%20applies%20to%20any%20other%20person%20%5BSection%2020(2)(a)%5D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThird%2C%20India%20suffers%20from%20the%20highest%20number%20of%20internet%20shutdowns%20in%20the%20world.%20These%20injuries%20have%20been%20felt%20acutely%20across%20our%20country%20by%20people%20resident%20in%20Manipur%2C%20Rajasthan%2C%20Odisha%2C%20West%20Bengal%2C%20Jammu%20%26amp%3B%20Kashmir%20etc.%20Here%2C%20the%20Telecommunications%20Bill%2C%202023%2C%20restates%20the%20power%20to%20impose%20internet%20blackouts%20without%20any%20statutory%20safeguards%2C%20despite%20court%20cases%20and%20recommendations%20by%20the%20Standing%20Committee%20for%20IT%20%5BSection%2020(2)(b)%5D.%20These%20could%20have%20been%20in%20the%20form%20of%20mere%20transparency%2C%20such%20as%20the%20duty%20of%20the%20state%20governments%20to%20send%20copies%20of%20orders%20to%20the%20Department%20of%20Telecommunications%20and%20then%20for%20the%20DOT%20to%20maintain%20a%20central%20directory%20of%20orders%2C%20however%2C%20is%20not%20part%20of%20the%20legislative%20text.%20This%20will%20also%20not%20be%20done%20under%20the%20rules%2C%20as%20the%20previous%20Telecom%20Suspension%20Rules%20will%20continue%20%5BSection%2061%5D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFourth%2C%20the%20Telecommunications%20Bill%2C%202023%20continues%20the%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Ekartavaya%20kaal%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%20style%20of%20imposing%20penalties%20on%20ordinary%20Indians%2C%20as%20has%20also%20found%20expression%20under%20the%20Data%20Protection%20Act%2C%202023.%20It%20prohibits%20%E2%80%9Cfalse%20particulars%2C%20suppress%5Bing%5D%20any%20material%20information%E2%80%A6%20while%20establishing%20their%20identity%20for%20availing%20telecommunications%20services%E2%80%9D.%20This%20means%20KYC%20may%20be%20required%20even%20for%20OTT%20applications%20like%20WhatsApp.%20In%20addition%20to%20this%2C%20there%20is%20a%20vague%20penalty%20for%20when%20people%20%E2%80%9Cfail%20to%20share%20information%20as%20required%20under%20this%20act%E2%80%9D%20%5BSection%2029%5D.%20The%20fine%20for%20this%20is%20Rs%2025%2C000%2C%20after%20which%20a%20daily%20fine%20of%20Rs%2050%2C000%20applies%20till%20you%20are%20compliant.%20Further%2C%20there%20is%20a%20marked%20preference%20for%20biometric%20identification%20%5BSec.%203(7)%5D.%20This%20may%20mean%20another%20attempt%20by%20the%20government%20to%20force%20people%20to%20use%20Aadhaar%20as%20the%20single%20point%20of%20sign-up%20(mandatory)%20despite%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20%3Cem%3EPuttaswamy%20vs%20Union%20of%20India%20%3C%2Fem%3Eclearly%20stating%20that%20this%20was%20impermissible.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20it%20merits%20use%20to%20examine%20the%20larger%20environment%20in%20which%20this%20Telecommunications%20Bill%2C%202023%2C%20is%20being%20passed.%20First%2C%20democracy%20is%20today%20suspended%20in%20India%20with%20a%20large%20number%20of%20Opposition%20MPs%20suspended%20from%20parliament.%20Meanwhile%2C%20other%20laws%20that%20increase%20state%20power%2C%20decrease%20accountability%20and%20transparency%20and%20threaten%20ordinary%20citizens%20are%20being%20passed.%20The%20fist%20of%20the%20state%20is%20becoming%20tighter%20on%20our%20digital%20lives%20with%20the%20Broadcasting%20Services%20Bill%2C%20Data%20Protection%20Act%20and%20Post%20Offices%20Bill%2C%20all%20of%202023%2C%20and%20the%20Criminal%20Procedure%20Identification%20Act%2C%202022%2C%20and%20the%20IT%20Rules%2C%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20all%20of%20these%20proposals%20and%20laws%2C%20the%20same%20model%20of%20vague%20drafting%2C%20centralisation%20of%20power%20through%20delegated%20rulemaking%20is%20proposed.%20Second%2C%20the%20government%20is%20failing%20to%20answer%20the%20clear%20challenges%20of%20rising%20inequality%20that%20manifest%20in%20digital%20India.%20For%20instance%2C%20it%20has%20failed%20to%20address%20or%20even%20acknowledge%20the%20sluggish%20pace%20of%20growth%20in%20the%20number%20of%20new%20mobile%20and%20data%20users%20in%20India.%20From%20double-digit%20growth%20rates%20through%202016%20to%202020%2C%20it%20slumped%20to%20about%204%25%20in%202021%20and%202022%2C%20according%20to%20Telecom%20Regulatory%20Authority%20of%20India%20data.%20In%20the%20first%20quarter%20of%202023%2C%20it%20grew%20just%201.7%25%20over%20the%20last%20quarter%20of%202022.%20Have%20we%20heard%20a%20word%20from%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Telecom%20on%20what%20is%20proposed%20to%20overcome%20this%3F%20There%20won%E2%80%99t%20be%20a%20word%20on%20it%20for%20there%20is%20nobody%20left%20or%20permitted%20in%20Parliament%20to%20raise%20these%20questions%20as%20the%20Telecommunications%20Bill%2C%202023%20is%20passed%20through%20a%20voice%20vote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShame%2C%20shame%2C%20shame.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EApar%20Gupta%20is%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20Internet%20Freedom%20Foundation.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20is%20excerpted%20from%20his%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2Fbb19a530-ad74-4420-92f3-229d2e8144a8%3Fj%3DeyJ1IjoiYWt5Mm8ifQ.6MWfvlP9rau_ovHEjX2OsfccTssIZEXNjPP_vKEvs5I%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2Fbb19a530-ad